Your Snowflake user does not have the required permissions for your Precog data pipeline to load data into your database.This can be resolved by following these steps, replacing "<pw>" with a password.

      Instructions

      Feel free to adapt these to your internal processes and preferences using the steps below as a guide. Please note however that the permissions detailed below are required for the user's default role.

      1) Log into Snowflake at https://app.snowflake.com/.
      2) Select “Classic Console” from the menu on the left.
      3) You may be asked to sign in again at this point.
      4) Select “Worksheets” from the toolbar at the top.
      5) Paste the following into a new worksheet:

      CREATE OR REPLACE DATABASE precog;
      CREATE OR REPLACE ROLE precog;
      CREATE OR REPLACE SCHEMA precog;
      CREATE WAREHOUSE precog WITH WAREHOUSE_SIZE = 'XSMALL' WAREHOUSE_TYPE = 'STANDARD' AUTO_SUSPEND = 300 AUTO_RESUME = TRUE;
      GRANT ALL ON WAREHOUSE precog TO ROLE precog;
      GRANT ALL ON DATABASE precog TO ROLE precog;
      GRANT ALL ON ALL SCHEMAS IN DATABASE precog TO ROLE precog;
      CREATE OR REPLACE USER precog PASSWORD = "<pw>" LOGIN_NAME = precog DISPLAY_NAME = precog MUST_CHANGE_PASSWORD = FALSE DEFAULT_WAREHOUSE = precog;
      GRANT ROLE precog TO USER precog;
      ALTER USER precog SET default_role=precog;
      GRANT USAGE ON ALL SCHEMAS IN DATABASE precog TO ROLE precog;
      GRANT USAGE ON FUTURE SCHEMAS IN DATABASE precog TO ROLE precog;
      GRANT ROLE precog TO ROLE sysadmin;

      6) Enable the “All queries” checkbox.
      7) Click “Run”.

      You now have a database, warehouse, and user named precog with the password <pw>.

      Return to your Precog data pipeline and click "Edit destination".

      Change the username, warehouse and database to precog

      Change the password to the password you specified in the prior steps.

      Click "Save" then try again.
